Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Loughnan Glossary
Author: LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page: 22
Edition:
Quote: cow-cocky or cow-spanker: Here there occurs an interesting variance between urban and rural diction. In the towns both terms denote a dairy farmer, but in the country a cow-cocky is a dairyfarmer and a cowspanker is the cowboy or cowman.
